properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County San Gabriel Valley
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 3:39AM PST until February 10 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to
40 mph expected.

* WHERE...San Gabriel Valley, especially below passes and canyons.

* WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roadways affected by strong cross winds
include the 10, 57, 60, 210, 605, and 710 freeways.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON PST MONDAY
